### Findings for `nsqd/topic.go`

| # | Type | Line | Severity | Description |
|---|------|------|----------|-------------|
| 1 | BUG | 385 | High | `channelMap` iterated without lock in `Close()` path — data race with concurrent `GetChannel()`/`DeleteExistingChannel()` which write under lock. The `Delete()` path (line 371) correctly locks; `Close()` does not. |
| 2 | BUG | 411-434 | Medium | `flush()` swallows all `writeMessageToBackend` errors, always returns `nil`. Messages that fail to persist during shutdown are silently lost. Also doesn't call `SetHealth()` unlike `put()`. |
| 3 | QUESTION | 486-494 | Low | `GenerateID()` has unbounded retry loop — persistent `NewGUID` failure would hang the caller indefinitely with no timeout or error escalation. |

**Assessment: FIX FIRST** — the unlocked map iteration in `Close()` is a data race.
